I'm not much of a pop music fan. Classical is more my thing, especially modernist classical music, Boulez, Stockhausen, also Phillip Glass,  John Cage, etc. I'm also deeply involved in the study of world music.  I came upon Charli by accident -- and i must say, despite my lack of interest in most pop or rock these days, this cut just blew me away. It's very rare that something this fresh and original comes along in ANY genre. Great singer, fantastic arrangement. So original. Keep up the great work, folks.
